## ALR  


ALR1. Pull the belt out fully and the lock mode changes from ELR to ALR.2. Verify that retractor makes a clicking sound as the belt slowly retracts. If no sound is heard, the lock mode has not changed to ALR. If necessary, repeat the above step 1.3. Verify that the belt locks when pulled.4. Verify that the lock mode changes to ELR when the belt fully retracts.5. If not as specified, replace the seat belt.  


